<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 2:58PM MDT  by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Weld
County through 345 PM MDT...
At 257 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Panorama Point, or 30 miles southwest of Kimball,
moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Pawnee Buttes around 315 PM MDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
